cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

This paper deals with image classification, which is a core problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of attributes as intermediate representations and the focus on parameter sharing suggest a machine learning approach (cs.LG). The proposed label-embedding framework involves learning a function that measures compatibility between an image and a label embedding, which is a typical task in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of textual descriptions as an alternative source of information is also relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the experiments involve datasets of animal images, which could be considered as multimedia (cs.MM).
